 WHITE RIVER – The Mpumalanga SAPS band entertained the dignitaries. Mpumalanga Provincial Police Commissioner  Lt Gen Mondli Zuma attended the event. “Members had been identified by their colleagues and the country as a whole for their hard work.” He said many challenges still lay ahead. “We work as a collective around the country and have even been asked by Mozambique to assist with the conflict happening in the northern part of their country. We have to keep being one step ahead and think out the box.” Maj Gen Zodwa Mokoena welcomed the guests and explained that the night was to congratulate the recepients  for their hard work and dedication. She quoted Winston Churchill’s words ” “You make a living by what you get; you make a life by what you give.”